From: Tim Fitzmaurice <tjf11@cus.cam.ac.uk>
Subject: Re: PRO/AH> Xenotransplantation, pig virus
I found the following citation on the subject...
Patience,C., Takeuchi,Y.& Weiss,R.A. Infection of human cells by an
endogenous retrovirus of pigs. Nature Medicine Vol.3 pp282-286 (March 1997)
There is a discussion of the issue in the News and Views of the same
Journal. Also in the same issue, and possibly having the author's think at
the moment, is the following paper Deacon et al,'Histological evidence of
fetal pig neural cell survival after transplantation into a patient with
Parkinson's disease'. Pages 350-353.
One wonders what effect the findings of the first paper will have on the
following up of the second.
---
Tim Fitzmaurice
